message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
title: "grounded-reasoning: zero-token, precision-guaranteed verification of LLM multi-hop relational reasoning"
abstract: >-
  A relation-algebra verifier for LLMs and agents. It checks a multi-hop
  relational claim before assertion with zero model tokens and a precision
  guarantee (accepts a claim iff a grounded proof path exists), plus a
  conformal mode giving distribution-free coverage under noisy graphs.
  Validated on real LLMs and the public CLUTRR benchmark; seven numerically
  verified theorems.
type: software
version: "0.1.4"
license: MIT
repository-code: "https://github.com/ALEXaquarius/grounded-reasoning"
keywords:
  - large-language-models
  - agents
  - hallucination
  - neuro-symbolic
  - conformal-prediction
  - knowledge-graph
